1
00:00:10,900 --> 00:00:12,033
<i> Miss Jade is my new boss.</i>

2
00:00:12,167 --> 00:00:15,433
<i>No! Olive is pretending to be
Jade.</i>

3
00:00:15,567 --> 00:00:18,633
<i>I don't care if I work for
Miss Olive or Miss Jade.</i>

4
00:00:18,767 --> 00:00:19,867
<i> Let go of my wife!</i>

5
00:00:24,100 --> 00:00:25,333
<i> Let's go, Dan!</i>

6
00:00:25,467 --> 00:00:27,000
<i> Someone kidnapped Mom.</i>

7
00:00:27,133 --> 00:00:27,933
<i> Who is it?</i>

8
00:00:28,067 --> 00:00:28,933
<i> I don't know.</i>

9
00:00:29,067 --> 00:00:29,633
<i> You have a stab wound?</i>

10
00:00:29,767 --> 00:00:31,367
<i> Why didn't you tell me?</i>

11
00:00:31,500 --> 00:00:32,400
<i> Help!</i>

12
00:00:32,533 --> 00:00:33,467
<i> Anybody home?</i>

13
00:00:33,600 --> 00:00:34,400
<i> Don't go.</i>

14
00:00:34,567 --> 00:00:35,200
<i> Stay here.</i>

15
00:00:35,333 --> 00:00:36,400
<i> Where are Emma and Danilo?</i>

16
00:00:36,533 --> 00:00:37,067
<i> I don't know.</i>

17
00:00:37,200 --> 00:00:38,333
<i> They escaped.</i>

18
00:00:38,467 --> 00:00:40,067
<i>- What are you doing there?
- Of course, I'm hiding!</i>

19
00:00:40,200 --> 00:00:43,733
<i>We were once a couple,
but we got separated.</i>

20
00:00:43,867 --> 00:00:45,600
<i> Your eyes say differently.</i>

21
00:00:45,733 --> 00:00:47,700
<i>The way you look at him
is full of love.</i>

22
00:00:47,833 --> 00:00:49,500
<i> Is what Ebing said true?</i>

23
00:00:49,633 --> 00:00:51,467
<i> Did you call me your husband?</i>

24
00:00:51,600 --> 00:00:54,333
<i>You also called me your wife
when you were defending me</i>

25
00:00:54,467 --> 00:00:56,533
<i>from the man last night, right?</i>

26
00:01:36,100 --> 00:01:39,667
Honestly, I'm envious of them.

27
00:01:41,267 --> 00:01:44,767
Because they're still together.

28
00:01:44,900 --> 00:01:51,067
I'm sure they've been
through a lot, too.

29
00:01:51,200 --> 00:01:52,567
But they didn't give up.

30
00:01:54,600 --> 00:01:55,867
Unlike us.

31
00:02:00,800 --> 00:02:05,667
Emma, maybe I was just so hurt.

32
00:02:09,167 --> 00:02:10,333
Because you left us.

33
00:02:12,333 --> 00:02:17,767
Weren't you the ones who left me
at the mental hospital?

34
00:02:17,933 --> 00:02:24,233
I prayed every day
that you'd believe me.

35
00:02:24,367 --> 00:02:27,667
That you would get me
out of that place.

36
00:02:27,800 --> 00:02:30,900
That you would believe me

37
00:02:31,033 --> 00:02:33,800
that Jade was behind
what happened to me.

38
00:02:36,500 --> 00:02:40,867
Danilo, it's okay if you still
don't want to believe.

39
00:02:43,167 --> 00:02:48,800
Logan helped me when I escaped
from the mental facility.

40
00:02:50,300 --> 00:02:58,067
I had to recover and endure
not seeing you and Mookie.

41
00:02:58,200 --> 00:02:59,900
I wanted to hug you so badly.

42
00:03:01,633 --> 00:03:03,667
You and Mookie were
too quick to judge me.

43
00:03:05,167 --> 00:03:06,700
You didn't listen to me.

44
00:03:06,833 --> 00:03:08,933
You drove me away.

45
00:03:09,067 --> 00:03:12,033
I could've explained what
really happened to me.

46
00:03:14,600 --> 00:03:16,867
But you denied me that chance.

47
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:18,333
You and Mookie hated me

48
00:03:18,467 --> 00:03:21,900
because you accused me of having
an affair with Logan...

49
00:03:22,067 --> 00:03:24,867
even though nothing's going on
between us.

50
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:28,600
You say that I left you
for Logan.

51
00:03:28,733 --> 00:03:32,400
The truth is,
you replaced me with Jade.

52
00:03:34,733 --> 00:03:37,067
Do you ever think of what
I would feel about that?

53
00:03:37,200 --> 00:03:40,000
Did you know how painful
that was for me?

54
00:03:47,733 --> 00:03:48,433
Emma...

55
00:03:50,067 --> 00:03:51,000
Emma, I'm sorry.

56
00:03:53,733 --> 00:03:59,333
I was carried away
by anger and jealousy.

57
00:03:59,500 --> 00:04:03,200
Because I can't bear seeing you
with another man.

58
00:04:08,167 --> 00:04:10,100
Emma, I know you.

59
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:13,733
I should be the first one
to believe you.

60
00:04:16,300 --> 00:04:18,167
I'm supposed to be the one
you can lean on.

61
00:04:18,300 --> 00:04:20,367
But, what did I do?

62
00:04:22,233 --> 00:04:23,500
What did I do?

63
00:04:23,633 --> 00:04:26,433
I abandoned you.

64
00:04:26,567 --> 00:04:30,767
So I hope you can
forgive me, Emma.

65
00:04:36,100 --> 00:04:37,867
I force myself
to get mad at you.

66
00:04:40,133 --> 00:04:42,400
But the truth is...

67
00:04:42,533 --> 00:04:43,633
The truth is...

68
00:04:47,100 --> 00:04:49,333
I miss you so much.

69
00:04:52,233 --> 00:04:56,233
Every night,
I find myself hoping...

70
00:04:56,367 --> 00:04:58,567
you were the one
lying next to me.

71
00:05:32,733 --> 00:05:34,200
Ligaya!

72
00:05:34,367 --> 00:05:35,233
I'm glad you're awake now.

73
00:05:37,667 --> 00:05:39,000
Ligaya!

74
00:05:39,133 --> 00:05:41,067
What breakfast do you want?
I just want to ask you that.

75
00:05:45,233 --> 00:05:47,100
What would you like
for breakfast?

76
00:05:47,233 --> 00:05:50,433
Tell me what happened to Emma.

77
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:53,000
Emma?

78
00:05:53,133 --> 00:05:55,300
Do you want Emma for breakfast?

79
00:05:55,433 --> 00:05:57,700
I don't have any news
about Emma.

80
00:05:57,833 --> 00:06:00,500
My boss is only
teaching her a lesson.

81
00:06:00,633 --> 00:06:03,900
You should be grateful
she didn't die the first time.

82
00:06:04,033 --> 00:06:06,667
It was your last born's fault.

83
00:06:06,800 --> 00:06:08,533
She often makes Miss Jade mad.

84
00:06:11,467 --> 00:06:13,167
Olive.

85
00:06:13,300 --> 00:06:15,867
Her name is Olive.

86
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:19,467
Jade isn't a bad person
like your boss.

87
00:06:19,600 --> 00:06:20,867
Fine.

88
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:22,167
Olive, it is.

89
00:06:22,300 --> 00:06:23,567
Miss Jade is Miss Olive.

90
00:06:28,767 --> 00:06:30,867
I don't get them.

91
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:32,400
Your children seem
to be crazy people.

92
00:06:35,600 --> 00:06:39,200
They were fighting over
the child at first.

93
00:06:39,333 --> 00:06:40,800
Now, it's the spouse
they're fighting over.

94
00:06:40,967 --> 00:06:41,967
Shut up.

95
00:06:46,500 --> 00:06:53,633
I'm grateful that Emma is alive,
as Olive said before.

96
00:06:53,767 --> 00:06:56,167
But now, I'm worried.

97
00:07:00,833 --> 00:07:04,267
Our family wouldn't be
falling apart

98
00:07:04,400 --> 00:07:06,667
if Olive didn't have mental
problems.

99
00:07:09,400 --> 00:07:12,033
<i> I want to get better so badly.</i>

100
00:07:12,167 --> 00:07:15,933
<i> But I don't know how.</i>

101
00:07:16,100 --> 00:07:18,800
<i> I consulted a doctor.</i>

102
00:07:21,800 --> 00:07:23,933
<i>I was told I have
a mental condition.</i>

103
00:07:27,700 --> 00:07:28,900
What about Ador?

104
00:07:30,833 --> 00:07:32,467
What really happened to him?

105
00:07:32,600 --> 00:07:35,467
You don't answer
whenever I ask you.

106
00:07:35,600 --> 00:07:36,333
Who's Ador?

107
00:07:38,667 --> 00:07:39,800
Is he the man you were with?

108
00:07:41,167 --> 00:07:46,333
I don't have any news about him.

109
00:07:46,467 --> 00:07:50,233
Miss Jade didn't tell me
to come back for him.

110
00:07:50,400 --> 00:07:52,433
I'm begging you to
come back for him.

111
00:07:54,467 --> 00:07:57,567
I want to make sure he's safe.

112
00:07:59,600 --> 00:08:01,700
I don't remember
his face anymore.

113
00:08:01,833 --> 00:08:04,233
And he's probably dead by now.

114
00:08:04,367 --> 00:08:05,833
I shot him, remember?

115
00:08:05,967 --> 00:08:07,100
That's what he got
for being a meddler.

116
00:08:07,233 --> 00:08:07,933
You animal.

117
00:08:10,467 --> 00:08:13,333
You're also a demon
like your boss.

118
00:08:13,467 --> 00:08:15,433
You have no conscience.

119
00:08:17,033 --> 00:08:18,433
Conscience, my foot.

120
00:08:20,400 --> 00:08:22,467
You talk too much, Miss.

121
00:08:22,633 --> 00:08:25,433
I'm only asking what
you like for breakfast.

122
00:08:25,567 --> 00:08:26,833
If you don't want to answer it,
then don't.

123
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:30,367
Eat whatever
I'll prepare for you.

124
00:08:50,467 --> 00:08:54,667
Yes, bro?

125
00:08:54,833 --> 00:08:57,033
What happened?

126
00:08:57,167 --> 00:08:59,767
You're lucky our boss
let you escape.

127
00:08:59,900 --> 00:09:02,067
If not, you'll be behind
bars again, you fool.

128
00:09:04,667 --> 00:09:05,667
Okay, okay.

129
00:09:05,800 --> 00:09:06,767
Be careful next time.

130
00:09:08,333 --> 00:09:09,467
Okay, bye.

131
00:09:15,867 --> 00:09:16,833
What did you say?

132
00:09:23,767 --> 00:09:25,167
Who were you talking to?

133
00:09:25,300 --> 00:09:26,333
Just a friend.

134
00:09:36,933 --> 00:09:39,600
What did you and Olive do
to Emma?

135
00:09:41,400 --> 00:09:45,933
Relax.

136
00:09:46,067 --> 00:09:48,033
Miss Jade's plan didn't happen.

137
00:09:48,167 --> 00:09:49,267
Emma is safe.

138
00:09:51,800 --> 00:09:53,633
Thank you.

139
00:09:53,767 --> 00:09:54,167
Son...

140
00:09:56,767 --> 00:09:57,900
I'm begging you.

141
00:09:59,300 --> 00:10:01,800
Please let me out.

142
00:10:01,967 --> 00:10:03,533
I'm sorry. I can't do that.

143
00:10:05,233 --> 00:10:06,133
Do you have a mother?

144
00:10:08,333 --> 00:10:10,400
What kind of a question is that?

145
00:10:10,533 --> 00:10:12,067
Of course, I do.

146
00:10:12,200 --> 00:10:14,500
Do you also have siblings?

147
00:10:14,633 --> 00:10:15,433
Yes.

148
00:10:15,567 --> 00:10:16,933
Wait, is this an interview?

149
00:10:19,400 --> 00:10:25,267
If your sibling locks up
and tortures your mother...

150
00:10:27,467 --> 00:10:29,200
won't you do anything?

151
00:10:32,967 --> 00:10:35,300
Can you let your mother suffer?

152
00:10:37,267 --> 00:10:38,833
No, right?

153
00:10:41,867 --> 00:10:44,500
So, I'm begging you, son.

154
00:10:47,533 --> 00:10:49,333
I'm really struggling.

155
00:10:58,200 --> 00:11:00,233
I'm having such a hard time.

156
00:11:00,367 --> 00:11:02,567
I'm sorry,
but I can't let you go.

157
00:11:07,867 --> 00:11:10,733
Please have mercy on me.

158
00:11:10,867 --> 00:11:12,733
Eat first.

159
00:11:12,867 --> 00:11:14,367
I'm begging you.

160
00:11:29,600 --> 00:11:31,533
Ma'am...

161
00:11:31,667 --> 00:11:33,200
do you need some help?

162
00:11:33,333 --> 00:11:34,933
No, I can manage.

163
00:11:35,067 --> 00:11:36,433
Just sit there.

164
00:11:43,167 --> 00:11:46,767
Emma, what's going on?

165
00:11:46,900 --> 00:11:50,833
You look so peaceful.

166
00:11:50,967 --> 00:11:52,767
Oh, nothing.

167
00:11:52,900 --> 00:11:56,067
Have you seen Danilo?

168
00:11:56,200 --> 00:11:59,367
He told me he would
only go for a walk.

169
00:11:59,500 --> 00:12:02,833
Yes, he and Bino
went to the stream.

170
00:12:02,967 --> 00:12:05,867
I think there's a
good reception there.

171
00:12:06,000 --> 00:12:07,900
He said he'd call your daughter.

172
00:12:13,467 --> 00:12:15,000
Hello, anybody home?

173
00:12:17,000 --> 00:12:18,800
- Jade?
- I knew it.

174
00:12:18,933 --> 00:12:20,033
Where's Danilo?

175
00:12:20,167 --> 00:12:21,733
Danilo!

176
00:12:21,867 --> 00:12:22,733
Love!

177
00:12:22,867 --> 00:12:24,867
-Emma.
-Jade! Don't you have any shame?

178
00:12:25,000 --> 00:12:26,800
Love!

179
00:12:26,933 --> 00:12:28,067
Jade!

180
00:12:31,867 --> 00:12:33,400
There's only one bed here.

181
00:12:35,100 --> 00:12:37,467
So, did you sleep together?

182
00:12:37,600 --> 00:12:39,700
Did something happen
between the two of you?

183
00:12:39,833 --> 00:12:41,767
Answer me!

184
00:12:41,900 --> 00:12:45,533
Did something happen
between you and Danilo?

185
00:12:45,667 --> 00:12:47,233
Let me go.

186
00:12:47,367 --> 00:12:48,400
I knew it!

187
00:12:48,567 --> 00:12:53,400
- You're such a flirt!
- Ouch!

188
00:12:53,533 --> 00:12:55,933
You're trying to steal
my fiancé!

189
00:12:56,067 --> 00:12:57,233
You're such a flirt!

190
00:12:57,367 --> 00:12:57,767
You whore!

191
00:12:57,900 --> 00:12:59,033
Stop!

192
00:12:59,167 --> 00:13:00,167
Don't hurt Emma!

193
00:13:00,300 --> 00:13:02,333
Let go of me!

194
00:13:02,467 --> 00:13:05,000
You're such a flirt!

195
00:13:22,833 --> 00:13:24,933
I'm sorry, son.

196
00:13:25,067 --> 00:13:28,300
I thought there was a
reception at the stream.

197
00:13:30,267 --> 00:13:32,267
Let's do this instead.

198
00:13:32,400 --> 00:13:35,633
We'll just escort you
out of the forest.

199
00:13:35,767 --> 00:13:38,400
You don't have to, Bino.

200
00:13:38,533 --> 00:13:41,367
You've done enough for us.

201
00:13:41,500 --> 00:13:44,033
Emma and I will take care of it.

202
00:13:44,167 --> 00:13:45,833
Okay, if that's what you want.

203
00:13:45,967 --> 00:13:48,200
Let's go.

204
00:13:48,333 --> 00:13:50,100
You're such a whore!

205
00:13:50,233 --> 00:13:51,400
You deserve that!

206
00:13:51,533 --> 00:13:52,567
Let go of her!

207
00:13:52,700 --> 00:13:53,533
That's enough!

208
00:13:56,433 --> 00:13:58,433
Won't you really shut up?

209
00:13:58,567 --> 00:13:59,433
Wait.

210
00:13:59,567 --> 00:14:01,167
- Hold on.
- I'm just controlling myself.

211
00:14:01,300 --> 00:14:02,433
Hold on.

212
00:14:02,567 --> 00:14:04,233
Are you okay?

213
00:14:04,367 --> 00:14:05,700
Don't be stupid, Logan.

214
00:14:06,933 --> 00:14:12,100
Why don't you ask what that
woman did before you defend her?

215
00:14:12,233 --> 00:14:13,700
What is it?

216
00:14:13,833 --> 00:14:16,300
What did she do to you
to hurt her again?

217
00:14:18,533 --> 00:14:21,100
Are you that stupid?

218
00:14:21,233 --> 00:14:26,133
While we were so worried the
whole night looking for them,

219
00:14:26,267 --> 00:14:32,200
this woman was so busy spreading
her legs for my fiancé!

220
00:14:32,367 --> 00:14:33,833
What?

221
00:14:33,967 --> 00:14:35,000
Ask her!

222
00:14:35,133 --> 00:14:36,533
Is what she said true?

223
00:14:48,067 --> 00:14:49,133
See that, Logan?

224
00:14:49,967 --> 00:14:51,767
She can't say a thing.

225
00:14:51,900 --> 00:14:54,200
Because it's true!

226
00:14:54,333 --> 00:14:57,433
I've been keeping my patience
with you for a while now!

227
00:14:57,567 --> 00:14:58,933
Let me go!

228
00:14:59,067 --> 00:15:00,567
Let go of me!

229
00:15:05,333 --> 00:15:07,267
I didn't steal anyone from you!

230
00:15:07,400 --> 00:15:09,433
If there's a homewrecker here,
it's you!

231
00:15:09,567 --> 00:15:11,700
How dare you!

232
00:15:11,833 --> 00:15:13,467
You're so shameless!

233
00:15:13,600 --> 00:15:14,800
Shameless!

234
00:15:14,933 --> 00:15:17,033
Let go of me!

235
00:15:17,167 --> 00:15:18,700
Danilo!

236
00:15:24,300 --> 00:15:25,967
Logan, restrain your woman!

237
00:15:26,100 --> 00:15:26,567
That's enough! Stop!

238
00:15:26,700 --> 00:15:28,100
You're so worthless!

239
00:15:28,233 --> 00:15:29,133
- Such a low-class vermin!
- Stop!

240
00:15:29,267 --> 00:15:30,367
That's enough!

241
00:15:30,500 --> 00:15:31,733
- Stop!
- Danilo.

242
00:15:31,867 --> 00:15:32,833
Ouch.

243
00:15:32,967 --> 00:15:34,333
Danilo.

244
00:15:34,500 --> 00:15:35,467
Ouch.

245
00:15:38,400 --> 00:15:39,400
What's going on?

246
00:15:44,033 --> 00:15:45,767
Why? What's happening to you?

247
00:15:45,900 --> 00:15:49,133
- Jade?
- Danilo, my stomach hurts.

248
00:15:49,267 --> 00:15:50,233
- Where is the way out?
- My stomach hurts!

249
00:15:50,367 --> 00:15:51,767
Let's bring her to the clinic.

250
00:15:51,900 --> 00:15:52,400
Let's go.

251
00:15:52,533 --> 00:15:54,333
Let's go, Jade.

252
00:15:54,467 --> 00:15:55,833
Ouch!

253
00:15:55,967 --> 00:15:56,500
Danilo!

254
00:15:58,600 --> 00:16:00,867
Please help me!

255
00:16:01,000 --> 00:16:02,767
Bring me to the hospital!

256
00:16:05,133 --> 00:16:06,767
Help me!

257
00:16:25,367 --> 00:16:27,400
I'm sorry for what happened.

258
00:16:27,533 --> 00:16:29,000
Thank you so much.

259
00:17:00,267 --> 00:17:02,600
Do you really need to do that?

260
00:17:02,733 --> 00:17:04,500
Yes.

261
00:17:04,633 --> 00:17:05,767
They're on their way back.

262
00:17:08,333 --> 00:17:09,533
I'm sorry.

263
00:17:26,833 --> 00:17:29,200
I would let you go
if I had a choice.

264
00:17:30,567 --> 00:17:33,100
My boss might harm my family
if I let you out.

265
00:17:57,867 --> 00:18:00,900
The manager said the resort's
security has been tightened.

266
00:18:01,033 --> 00:18:04,100
We'll update you on
our investigation.

267
00:18:04,233 --> 00:18:05,233
Thank you.

268
00:18:05,367 --> 00:18:07,867
You're welcome.
I'll go ahead now, Sir.

269
00:18:13,300 --> 00:18:15,267
You haven't answered
my question yet.

270
00:18:17,500 --> 00:18:19,767
Did something really happen
between you and Danilo?

271
00:18:22,200 --> 00:18:23,067
Nothing happened.

272
00:18:26,533 --> 00:18:27,867
We just kissed.

273
00:18:32,467 --> 00:18:33,767
You allowed him?

274
00:18:35,867 --> 00:18:37,967
Is that the reason you
didn't accept my feelings?

275
00:18:38,967 --> 00:18:40,533
Because you still love Danilo?

276
00:18:45,233 --> 00:18:46,467
Logan, sorry.

277
00:18:47,467 --> 00:18:49,433
Yes, I made a mistake.

278
00:18:50,833 --> 00:18:52,400
I got confused.

279
00:18:52,533 --> 00:18:54,133
I thought I no longer
loved Danilo.

280
00:18:54,267 --> 00:18:57,733
So, I shifted my feelings
to you.

281
00:18:58,767 --> 00:19:01,767
But you can't easily teach
the heart what to feel.

282
00:19:01,900 --> 00:19:03,667
Emma...

283
00:19:03,800 --> 00:19:05,667
Danilo already has Jade!

284
00:19:06,900 --> 00:19:09,067
He has already replaced you.

285
00:19:09,200 --> 00:19:11,133
Even worse, with your sister!

286
00:19:12,900 --> 00:19:14,667
Yes, he made a mistake.

287
00:19:14,800 --> 00:19:17,167
But it's because
Jade fooled her.

288
00:19:17,300 --> 00:19:20,400
Jade poisoned his mind.

289
00:19:20,533 --> 00:19:22,333
Logan, we've already talked.

290
00:19:30,367 --> 00:19:35,833
<i>Please forgive me, Emma,
for pushing you away.</i>

291
00:19:35,967 --> 00:19:38,967
<i> I only want to be heard.</i>

292
00:19:41,867 --> 00:19:43,200
<i> Yes, Emma.</i>

293
00:19:45,133 --> 00:19:50,433
<i>Let's talk it through
once we get out of here.</i>

294
00:19:50,567 --> 00:19:54,333
<i> So we can clear things out.</i>

295
00:19:54,467 --> 00:19:57,667
<i>I'll listen to
everything you say.</i>

296
00:19:57,800 --> 00:20:01,000
<i>And I'll explain why Jade
and I ended up together.</i>

297
00:20:11,233 --> 00:20:17,567
Logan, thank you
for all your help.

298
00:20:17,700 --> 00:20:20,833
I'm sorry that I can't
reciprocate all the love

299
00:20:20,967 --> 00:20:22,200
you're giving me.

300
00:20:24,167 --> 00:20:25,900
I hope you understand.

301
00:20:28,933 --> 00:20:33,567
I'll move out once we get back
to Manila.

302
00:20:33,700 --> 00:20:37,100
I don't want to take advantage
of your kindness.

303
00:20:44,733 --> 00:20:45,400
No.

304
00:20:47,033 --> 00:20:47,833
No, Emma.

305
00:20:52,067 --> 00:20:53,933
Nothing will change between us.

306
00:20:56,167 --> 00:20:59,267
Even if we don't end up
together,

307
00:21:00,967 --> 00:21:03,367
I still want to keep
our friendship.

308
00:21:05,033 --> 00:21:05,867
So, no.

309
00:21:07,067 --> 00:21:08,767
You're not leaving my house.

310
00:21:10,733 --> 00:21:13,133
And my feelings for you...

311
00:21:15,767 --> 00:21:17,067
I won't push it for now.

312
00:21:19,433 --> 00:21:21,267
Thank you, Logan.

313
00:21:35,300 --> 00:21:38,367
The woman you'll end up with
will be so lucky.

314
00:21:43,100 --> 00:21:44,533
I'll get some fresh air outside.

315
00:21:59,133 --> 00:21:59,733
Hey!

316
00:21:59,867 --> 00:22:00,433
Do that later.

317
00:22:00,567 --> 00:22:01,667
Come on!

318
00:22:01,800 --> 00:22:03,700
Tell me,

319
00:22:03,833 --> 00:22:07,200
are you and Dan finally going to
have a heart-to-heart talk?

320
00:22:07,333 --> 00:22:08,367
You're something else!

321
00:22:08,933 --> 00:22:10,033
Be quiet!

322
00:22:10,167 --> 00:22:11,867
Someone might hear you.

323
00:22:12,000 --> 00:22:15,267
Sorry, I'm just excited.

324
00:22:15,433 --> 00:22:18,100
So when will you talk?

325
00:22:18,233 --> 00:22:19,000
I don't know yet.

326
00:22:19,133 --> 00:22:22,067
Something happened
to Jade, remember?

327
00:22:22,200 --> 00:22:25,467
That witch is just
putting on an act.

328
00:22:25,600 --> 00:22:27,333
She's threatened.

329
00:22:27,467 --> 00:22:28,567
She better be.

330
00:22:28,700 --> 00:22:29,967
She should be nervous.

331
00:22:30,100 --> 00:22:33,100
Because Danilo will
find out the truth.

332
00:22:36,667 --> 00:22:38,333
Is it okay with Logan?

333
00:22:40,033 --> 00:22:42,767
That's what he said.

334
00:22:42,900 --> 00:22:45,967
That's hard to believe.

335
00:22:46,100 --> 00:22:50,900
Will he give up without
putting up a fight?

336
00:22:51,067 --> 00:22:53,867
Flor, please stop
thinking that way.

337
00:22:54,000 --> 00:22:56,167
Logan is a good person.

338
00:22:56,300 --> 00:23:00,300
And he said he understood
my feelings.

339
00:23:04,067 --> 00:23:07,600
I thought you'd
finally be a couple.

340
00:23:07,733 --> 00:23:09,833
But it's okay.

341
00:23:09,967 --> 00:23:11,867
Many girls are dying
to be with you.

342
00:23:13,800 --> 00:23:15,833
Emma is all I want.

343
00:23:17,533 --> 00:23:21,767
I won't let her and Danilo
get back together.

344
00:23:23,067 --> 00:23:25,833
Does it mean you
haven't given up yet?

345
00:23:29,500 --> 00:23:33,700
Do you think I asked her
to stay here...

346
00:23:35,200 --> 00:23:36,333
for nothing?

347
00:23:52,133 --> 00:23:53,267
What are you doing here?

348
00:23:53,400 --> 00:23:56,433
Don't tell me you'll also
make a scene like Emma did?

349
00:23:58,933 --> 00:24:01,800
Olive, is that you?

350
00:24:01,933 --> 00:24:03,833
<i> You're so beautiful, Olive.</i>

351
00:24:03,967 --> 00:24:05,567
<i> You have such a gentle face.</i>

352
00:24:05,700 --> 00:24:10,233
<i>Like me, who no one would think
is hiding a demon within.</i>

353
00:24:10,367 --> 00:24:13,300
I won't let you talk to Emma.

354
00:24:13,433 --> 00:24:15,267
You will never see her again!

355
00:24:15,400 --> 00:24:16,433
Jade, sorry,

356
00:24:16,567 --> 00:24:19,233
but you can't stop me
and Mookie.

357
00:24:19,367 --> 00:24:20,267
No.

358
00:24:20,400 --> 00:24:22,900
I'm sorry, but I no longer want
to marry you.

359
00:24:23,033 --> 00:24:25,033
Damn you, Danilo!

360
00:24:25,167 --> 00:24:29,033
Mommy Jade was so furious
that she yelled at me.

361
00:24:29,200 --> 00:24:31,767
For a moment, I thought
she was Mommy Olive.

362
00:24:31,900 --> 00:24:35,900
The glare in her eyes,
the way her jaw trembled...

363
00:24:36,033 --> 00:24:38,033
she really reminded me
of Mommy Olive.

364
00:24:38,167 --> 00:24:41,933
Don't tell me you think
Aunt Jade is your Mommy Olive?

365
00:24:42,067 --> 00:24:44,433
You only spent a night
with Emma,

366
00:24:44,567 --> 00:24:48,900
and you totally forgot
everything I did for you.

367
00:24:49,033 --> 00:24:53,700
Tell me, did you ever love me?
